evidence: The microhardness of the as-cast NbZrTi alloy is HV 372. At room temperature, both alloys do not break during the compressive tests and exhibit excellent plastic properties, which are seldom found for bcc-typed high-entropy alloys. For the NbZrTi alloy, the grains have the size of 300 lm.

The microhardness of the as-cast NbHfZrTi alloy is HV 351. At room temperature, both alloys do not break during the compressive tests and exhibit excellent plastic properties, which are seldom found for bcc-typed high-entropy alloys. For the NbHfZrTi alloy, the grain size is about 50 lm.
